    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM MGM SPRING BRAKE - CAM BRAKE ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CAM BRAKE ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The last half of an air chamber stroke is less efficient than the first half. Therefore, the
                        following adjustments are recommended for maximum efficiency.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
            <title>BRAKES OFF - NOT APPLIED (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0402021">Figure 21</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <para>Angle must always be greater than 90&#176; due to various slack adjuster lengths and installation
                setups. Refer to GROUP 04 - AIR BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended angle.
            </para>
            <para>Maximum stroke should be as short as possible without brakes dragging.</para>
            <figure id="f0402021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0402030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Brakes Off - Not Applied</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
